This project is published so people can play it, read it, and learn from it. It is not public domain.
You may use the covered material for noncommercial purposes, and you may modify it privately, but you
may not publish a modified or derived version, and you may not use it commercially, without written
permission. If you are unsure whether your intended use is allowed, ask first — contact details are at
the end.

This summary is a convenience. The terms below are what govern.


