4. Noncommercial purpose
------------------------

Any noncommercial purpose is a permitted purpose. A purpose is commercial if it is directed toward
commercial advantage or monetary compensation, whether or not any money actually changes hands. In
particular, the following are commercial and are not permitted:

  a. Selling, renting, or licensing access to the covered material or to anything derived from it.
  b. Publishing a game, experience, or product that incorporates the covered material and that sells
     goods, currency, passes, subscriptions, advertising, or any other paid item or placement.
  c. Packaging or selling the covered material as part of another product or service.
  d. Using the covered material to promote a separate commercial product or service.


5. Personal uses
